# Internationalization (i18n)

Portal supports multiple languages using next-intl with locale-based routing and comprehensive translation management.

## Architecture

### Configuration Files
- `i18n/routing.ts`: Core routing configuration with supported locales
- `i18n/navigation.ts`: Localized navigation helpers and utilities  
- `i18n/request.ts`: Server-side locale detection and request handling
- `middleware.ts`: Locale routing middleware for automatic detection

### Translation Structure
- `i18n/locales/en.json`: English (default) - comprehensive base translations
- `i18n/locales/zh-CN.json`: Chinese Simplified - mainland China
- `i18n/locales/zh-HK.json`: Chinese Traditional - Hong Kong

### Route Structure
- `app/[locale]/`: All routes include locale parameter
- Automatic locale detection from Accept-Language header
- Fallback to default locale (en) for unsupported languages
- URL structure: `/en/dashboard`, `/zh-CN/dashboard`, `/zh-HK/dashboard`

## Translation Management

### JSON Structure
```json
{
  "Common": {
    "welcome": "Welcome",
    "loading": "Loading...",
    "error": "An error occurred"
  },
  "Dashboard": {
    "title": "Dashboard",
    "analytics": {
      "totalContacts": "Total Contacts",
      "revenue": "Revenue"
    }
  },
  "CRM": {
    "contacts": {
      "title": "Contacts",
      "addNew": "Add New Contact",
      "fields": {
        "firstName": "First Name",
        "lastName": "Last Name",
        "email": "Email Address"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Nested Namespaces
Organize translations by feature areas:
- `Common`: Shared UI elements, buttons, messages
- `Dashboard`: Dashboard-specific content
- `CRM`: Contact and company management
- `Auth`: Authentication and user management
- `Tasks`: Task management features
- `Calendar`: Calendar and event features

## Usage Patterns

### Component Translation
```tsx
import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl';

export default function ContactForm() {
  const t = useTranslations('CRM.contacts');
  const common = useTranslations('Common');
  
  return (
    <form>
      <h2>{t('title')}</h2>
      <input placeholder={t('fields.firstName')} />
      <button>{common.save}</button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

### Server Component Translation
```tsx
import { getTranslations } from 'next-intl/server';

export default async function ServerPage({ 
  params: { locale } 
}: {
  params: { locale: string }
}) {
  const t = await getTranslations('Dashboard');
  
  return <h1>{t('title')}</h1>;
}
```

### Dynamic Translation Keys
```tsx
const t = useTranslations('CRM.contacts.status');
const status = 'active'; // dynamic value
const statusText = t(status); // translates 'active' key
```

### Pluralization
```tsx
const t = useTranslations('Common');
const count = 5;

// Using ICU message format for plurals
const message = t('itemCount', { count });
// Translation: "itemCount": "{count, plural, =0 {No items} =1 {One item} other {# items}}"
```

## Routing & Navigation

### Localized Navigation
```tsx
import { Link, redirect } from '@/i18n/navigation';
import { useRouter } from '@/i18n/navigation';

export function LocalizedNavigation() {
  const router = useRouter();
  
  return (
    <nav>
      <Link href="/dashboard">{t('dashboard')}</Link>
      <Link href="/crm/contacts">{t('contacts')}</Link>
      <button onClick={() => router.push('/settings')}>
        {t('settings')}
      </button>
    </nav>
  );
}
```

### Locale Switching
```tsx
import { useLocale } from 'next-intl';
import { useRouter, usePathname } from '@/i18n/navigation';

export function LocaleSwitcher() {
  const locale = useLocale();
  const router = useRouter();
  const pathname = usePathname();
  
  const switchLocale = (newLocale: string) => {
    router.replace(pathname, { locale: newLocale });
  };
  
  return (
    <select value={locale} onChange={(e) => switchLocale(e.target.value)}>
      <option value="en">English</option>
      <option value="zh-CN">简体中文</option>
      <option value="zh-HK">繁體中文</option>
    </select>
  );
}
```

## Middleware Configuration

```tsx
// middleware.ts
import createIntlMiddleware from 'next-intl/middleware';
import { routing } from './i18n/routing';

const intlMiddleware = createIntlMiddleware(routing);

export default async function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
  // Handle internationalization
  const response = intlMiddleware(request);
  
  // Additional middleware logic (auth, etc.)
  return response;
}

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/', '/(zh-CN|zh-HK|en)/:path*']
};
```

## Date & Number Formatting

### Locale-Aware Formatting
```tsx
import { useFormatter } from 'next-intl';

export function FormattedContent() {
  const format = useFormatter();
  
  const date = new Date();
  const price = 1299.99;
  
  return (
    <div>
      <p>{format.dateTime(date, 'short')}</p>
      <p>{format.number(price, 'currency')}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Timezone Handling
```tsx
const format = useFormatter();
const userTimezone = 'Asia/Hong_Kong';

const formattedDate = format.dateTime(date, {
  timeZone: userTimezone,
  dateStyle: 'medium',
  timeStyle: 'short'
});
```

## Best Practices

### Translation Key Organization
- Use nested namespaces for better organization
- Keep keys descriptive and context-aware
- Avoid overly deep nesting (max 3-4 levels)
- Use consistent naming conventions

### Content Management
- Implement translation validation in CI/CD
- Use translation management tools for non-developers
- Maintain translation completeness tracking
- Regular translation review and updates

### Performance Optimization
- Lazy load translation files when possible
- Use tree-shaking for unused translations
- Implement efficient caching strategies
- Monitor bundle size impact of translations

### Development Workflow
- Extract translatable strings during development
- Use translation keys instead of hardcoded text
- Implement missing translation detection
- Provide development-time translation helpers

## RTL Support (Future)

While not currently implemented, the architecture supports RTL languages:
- CSS logical properties usage
- Directional icon handling
- Layout adaptation for RTL reading patterns
- Bidirectional text support
